HEADWORD: Endotheca
<hw>En`do*the"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>'e`ndon</grk> within + <grk>qh`kh</grk> a case, box, fr. <?/ to
place.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>The tissue which partially
fills the interior of the interseptal chambers of most madreporarian
corals. It usually consists of a series of oblique transverse septa, one
above another.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>En`do*the"cal</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endothecium</ent>⟦br⟧
